<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-25T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-25T12:00:00-05:00" n="1138" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1138">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.2367/16: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-25T19:00:00+02:00">August 25,
                                    1943—7 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 8:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1471. I have been informed today that Turkish Government has accepted
                            validity of argument that the seven survivors of the crew of the
                            Liberator which crashed off coast of southern Turkey be regarded as
                            “shipwrecked mariners” (my 1388R, August 8) and has ordered their
                                release.<note n="35" xml:id="d1138fn35">In telegram No. 1596,
                                September 21, 10 a.m., the Ambassador reported that the 15 aviators
                                in question had been released by the Turkish Government
                                (811.2367/19).</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>Please inform General Arnold.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Cairo for General Breton [<hi rend="italic">Brereton</hi>].<note n="36" xml:id="d1138fn36">Maj. Gen. Lewis H.
                                Brereton, Commander, U.S. Army Forces in the Middle East
                                (USAFIME).</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>